# Local wiki (MkDocs)

**Source:** [`docs/wiki/`](../../docs/wiki/) — Markdown + [`mkdocs.yml`](../../docs/wiki/mkdocs.yml).

**Build (repo root):** `pip install -r requirements-wiki.txt` then `mkdocs build -f docs/wiki/mkdocs.yml` (output `docs/wiki/site/`, gitignored). **Preview:** `mkdocs serve -f docs/wiki/mkdocs.yml` or `scripts/serve-wiki.ps1`.

**Contents:** Umbrella overview is [`Silicon-Sites-Submodules-Wiki.md`](../../docs/wiki/Silicon-Sites-Submodules-Wiki.md). **Per-submodule deep wikis** are generated Markdown under [`docs/wiki/generated/submodules/`](../../docs/wiki/generated/submodules/) via [`scripts/generate-submodule-wikis.py`](../../scripts/generate-submodule-wikis.py) (run from repo root; `scripts/build-wiki.ps1` / `build-wiki.sh` run it before `mkdocs build`). Commit regenerated `.md` when submodule trees change. Extend the wiki by adding hand-written Markdown under `docs/wiki/` and `nav` entries in `mkdocs.yml` when needed.

Do **not** assume DeepWiki, Devin hosted wiki, or `mcp.deepwiki.com` for this repository; documentation is maintained in git and built locally.
